The paper proposes a method for automatically determining the number of neurons in each layer of a deep network during learning. This falls under the category of machine learning, specifically deep learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of deep networks in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which are also likely categories. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for this approach to be used in constrained platforms, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
